Assets - 2015

Did a lawmaker have an asset worth more than $1,000 at the end of the calendar year? Did it generate over $200 of annual income? Did this person buy, sell or exchange something valued over $1,000? If so, it must be disclosed.

Any legal ownership a person has in a company or property is classified as an asset, including brokerage accounts, corporate bonds and stocks. (Note: Filers are not required to provide detail about mutual fund holdings or report the value of their residence unless it generates income.)
